@startuml class_diagram

title Calculator — Class Diagram

package "src" {

    class Calculator {
        + add(a, b) : float
        + subtract(a, b) : float
        + multiply(a, b) : float
        + divide(a: float, b: float) : float
        + power(base: float, exponent: float) : float
        + square(a: float) : float
        + cube(a: float) : float
        + square_root(a: float) : float
        + cube_root(a: float) : float
        + log(a: float) : float
        + ln(a: float) : float
        + factorial(n: int) : int
    }

    class TooManyAttemptsError {
    }

    class "error_logger" as ErrLog <<module>> {
        - ERROR_LOG_FILE : str = "calculator_errors.log"
        - _LOG_FORMAT : str
        + get_error_logger(log_file: str) : Logger
    }

    class "__main__" as Main <<module>> {
        - OPERATIONS : dict
        - MAX_ATTEMPTS : int = 5
        - HISTORY_FILE : str = "history.txt"
        + _fmt_num(x) : str
        + _format_entry(method_name: str, operands: tuple, result) : str
        + _write_history(history: list[str], path: str) : None
        + _read_number(prompt: str, max_attempts: int, error_logger) : float
        + run_session(calc: Calculator, history_file: str, error_log_file: str) : None
        + main() : None
    }

    Main --> Calculator : uses
    Main ..> TooManyAttemptsError : raises / catches
    Main --> ErrLog : get_error_logger()
}

note right of Calculator
  Validation rules:
  divide: b != 0
  square_root: a >= 0
  cube_root: handles negative (sign-preserving)
  log: a > 0
  ln: a > 0
  factorial: n >= 0, integer, not bool
end note

note right of ErrLog
  ERROR_LOG_FILE = "calculator_errors.log"
  get_error_logger() returns a Logger writing
  ERROR-level records to the given file.
  Logger name is derived from the file path
  for test isolation (unique logger per path).
  Log format: timestamp [LEVEL] message
  Kept separate from history.txt so normal
  operation records and errors never mix.
end note

note right of Main
  OPERATIONS dict maps menu keys (1..12)
  to (method_name, operand_count, label).
  run_session() loops until user enters "0".
  MAX_ATTEMPTS = 5: session terminates after
  5 consecutive invalid menu choices or 5
  consecutive invalid number inputs.
  _read_number() raises TooManyAttemptsError
  when the attempt limit is reached.
  History: each successful calculation is
  appended to a list in function-call style
  (e.g. add(2, 3) = 5). On session exit,
  _write_history() saves the list to
  HISTORY_FILE ("history.txt"). The user
  can view history mid-session via "h".
  Errors logged: invalid menu choice,
  too many invalid choices, invalid number
  inputs, factorial non-integer, calculation
  errors (ValueError/ZeroDivisionError/TypeError).
end note

@enduml
